# Usage

## Admonition Types

Stencila supports nine admonition types, each with semantic meaning:

- **Note**: Neutral information or side notes
- **Info**: Informational content
- **Tip**: Helpful suggestions or best practices
- **Important**: Critical information requiring attention
- **Success**: Positive outcomes or completion states
- **Failure**: Negative outcomes or error states
- **Warning**: Cautionary information
- **Danger**: Critical warnings about potentially harmful actions
- **Error**: Error messages or problematic states

Each type receives a distinct icon via CSS `::before` pseudo-element using [Bootstrap Icons](https://icons.getbootstrap.com/):

- **Note**: Pencil icon - implies note-taking and annotation
- **Info**: Info-circle icon - standard information symbol
- **Tip**: Fire icon - implies "hot tip" and useful insights
- **Important**: Megaphone icon - conveys announcement and urgency
- **Success**: Check-circle icon - indicates completion and positive outcome
- **Failure**: X-circle icon - indicates failure and negative outcome
- **Warning**: Exclamation-triangle icon - universal warning symbol
- **Danger**: Exclamation-diamond icon - diamond/rotated square with exclamation mark
- **Error**: X-octagon icon - stop sign shape with strong error signal

Icons can be customized by overriding the icon size or by replacing the icon content entirely in custom themes.

## Collapsible Behavior

Admonitions support optional collapsible behavior using native HTML `<details>` and `<summary>` elements:

- **Non-collapsible**: Default behavior, always visible
- **Collapsible**: When `is-folded` attribute is present
  - `is-folded="true"`: Initially collapsed
  - `is-folded="false"`: Initially expanded, but user can collapse

The chevron toggle icon appears automatically on collapsible admonitions via CSS `::after` pseudo-element and rotates on open/close. This is pure CSS with no JavaScript required.

## Integration with Semantic Tokens

Admonitions leverage the design system's semantic tokens for automatic theming:

- **Automatic responsive behavior**: Spacing uses `--content-spacing` which provides desktop (2rem), tablet (1.5rem), mobile (1rem), and print (0.5rem) variants without manual media queries
- **Border consistency**: Border color references `--border-color-default` with automatic dark mode support
- **Typography inheritance**: Font sizes and weights reference semantic typography tokens for system-wide consistency
- **Mobile optimization**: Horizontal padding automatically reduces on mobile devices

## Icon Customization

Icons are rendered via CSS `::before` pseudo-elements using SVG mask-image technique with [Bootstrap Icons](https://icons.getbootstrap.com/). This allows flexible color control through a single token.

**Size control**: Use `--admonition-icon-size` to scale icons proportionally to the title text. The default `1.25em` makes icons slightly larger than the surrounding text.

**Spacing control**: Use `--admonition-icon-gap` to adjust space between the icon and title text.

**Color control**: Icons derive their color from type-specific color tokens (e.g., `--admonition-warning-color`). Change one token to update icon, border, and background colors together.

**Custom icons**: Replace icons by overriding the `mask-image` property for specific admonition types. Use URL-encoded SVG data URIs for the icon content. All Bootstrap Icons are available from [icons.getbootstrap.com](https://icons.getbootstrap.com/).

## Color Derivation

The design uses a **single base color per type** to derive all visual elements:

- **Icon color**: Uses base color directly via CSS mask-image
- **Border**: All borders (top, right, bottom, left) mixed with transparent at 40% opacity (controlled by `--admonition-border-opacity`) for softer, lighter appearance
- **Title text**: Base color mixed with black at 95% (controlled by `--admonition-title-color-weight`)
- **Title background**: Base color tinted with transparency at 12.5% (controlled by `--admonition-title-background-tint`) using `color-mix()`
- **Content background**: Base color tinted with transparency at 0% by default (controlled by `--admonition-content-background-tint`), allowing theme authors to opt-in to tinted content backgrounds
- **Title bottom border**: Uses same border opacity for visual separation

This approach ensures visual consistency and minimal token overhead. Changing `--admonition-warning-color` updates the icon, borders, title text, and backgrounds automatically. The opacity-based border derivation creates lighter, softer borders in both light and dark modes by making them semi-transparent rather than darkening them.

**Example:**
```css
:root {
  /* Change all Warning visual elements with one token */
  --admonition-warning-color: var(--color-orange-600);
}
```

## Mobile Optimization

Mobile devices automatically receive optimized spacing:

- All spacing scales automatically through `--content-spacing` calculation
- Chevron toggle remains fully functional on touch devices

